{# --- Tunneled Pleural Catheter Instructions --- #}
{% macro tpc_discharge_instructions(followup_timeframe='2 weeks') %}
DISCHARGE INSTRUCTIONS FOR TUNNELED PLEURAL CATHETER (PleurX)

DAILY DRAINAGE INSTRUCTIONS:
1. Wash hands thoroughly before handling the catheter
2. Gather supplies: drainage kit, alcohol pads, gloves
3. Clean the valve cap with alcohol pad for 15 seconds
4. Connect the drainage line to the catheter valve
5. Open the clamp to allow drainage
6. Monitor drainage amount and color
7. Stop drainage when flow stops or if experiencing chest pain/shortness of breath
8. Close clamp and disconnect drainage line
9. Clean valve cap again with alcohol pad
10. Replace valve cap securely
11. Record amount and color of fluid drained

WHEN TO CALL:
- Fever >100.4°F
- Increasing shortness of breath
- Chest pain during or after drainage
- Redness, swelling, or drainage at catheter site
- Catheter appears to be coming out
- Less than 50ml drainage for 3 consecutive sessions
- Sudden increase in drainage amount

EMERGENCY SITUATIONS:
- Catheter completely falls out
- Severe chest pain or difficulty breathing
- Air leak from catheter (pinch tubing and go to ER immediately)

FOLLOW-UP:
- Scheduled appointment in {{ followup_timeframe }}
- Bring drainage log to all appointments
{% endmacro %}


