{# --- PEG Discharge Instructions --- #}
{% macro peg_discharge_instructions() %}
PEG DISCHARGE INSTRUCTIONS:

WOUND CARE:
- Keep site clean and dry
- Change dressing daily for first week
- Monitor for signs of infection (redness, swelling, drainage, fever)

FLUSHING PROTOCOLS:
- Flush with 30-60 mL water before and after each feed
- Flush with 30 mL water before and after medications
- Flush every 4-6 hours if not in use

MEDICATIONS:
- Crush pills thoroughly and mix with water
- Use liquid formulations when available
- Do not mix medications together

DIET:
- Begin with clear liquids as tolerated
- Advance to formula as directed
- Maintain adequate hydration

FOLLOW-UP:
- Return to clinic as scheduled
- Contact provider for any concerns
{% endmacro %}
